## Multi-Line Commit Examples

### With Body

```bash
✨ feat(tenants): add export functionality

Add CSV export button to tenants table that allows
admins to download filtered tenant data. The export
includes all visible columns and respects current
filters and search terms.

- Add export button to DataTableToolbar
- Implement export mutation in query layer
- Add permission check for export action
- Handle file download in browser

Closes #123
```

### With Breaking Change

```bash
✨ feat(api)!: migrate to new authentication system

BREAKING CHANGE: The authentication API has been
completely rewritten. All clients must update to
use the new token format and refresh mechanism.

Migration guide: docs/migration/auth-v2.md

Closes #456
```

### With Multiple Issues

```bash
🐛 fix(table): resolve sorting and pagination bugs

Fix issue where table sorting would reset pagination
and vice versa. Also resolves edge case where empty
state would not display correctly.

Fixes #123
Fixes #456
Closes #789
```

## Best Practices

### 1. One Logical Change Per Commit

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(auth): add password reset flow
🐛 fix(table): resolve pagination issue
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
✨ feat: add auth and fix table bugs
```

### 2. Use Specific Scopes

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(tenants): add bulk delete
🐛 fix(data-table): resolve column sorting
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
✨ feat: add bulk delete
🐛 fix: resolve sorting
```

### 3. Write Clear Descriptions

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(forms): add validation error messages
🐛 fix(api): handle 404 responses gracefully
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
✨ feat(forms): update
🐛 fix(api): fix bug
```

### 4. Keep It Short

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(dashboard): add analytics widget
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
✨ feat(dashboard): add comprehensive analytics widget with real-time data visualization and customizable charts
```

### 5. Use Imperative Mood

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(auth): add login button
🐛 fix(api): handle errors
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
✨ feat(auth): added login button
🐛 fix(api): handles errors
```

### 6. Include Emoji

**✅ DO:**

```bash
✨ feat(auth): add login
🐛 fix(table): resolve bug
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```bash
feat(auth): add login
fix(table): resolve bug
```

## Commit Message Template

Use this template when writing commits:

```
<emoji> <type>(<scope>): <short description>

<longer description if needed>

<footer if needed>
```

## Quick Reference

### Most Common Types

```bash
✨ feat:     New feature
🐛 fix:      Bug fix
♻️ refactor: Code refactoring
📝 docs:     Documentation
✅ test:     Tests
🔧 chore:    Maintenance
⚡ perf:     Performance
💄 style:    Code style
```

### Breaking Changes

Add `!` after type/scope:

```bash
✨ feat(api)!: change authentication
```

Or use footer:

```bash
✨ feat(api): change authentication

BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
```

## Integration with Git

### Pre-commit Hook (Optional)

You can add a pre-commit hook to validate commit messages:

```bash
#!/bin/sh
# .git/hooks/commit-msg

commit_msg=$(cat "$1")
pattern="^(✨|🐛|📝|💄|♻️|⚡|✅|🔧|👷|📦|⏪|🔒|🌐|♿|🎨|🗄️|⚙️) (feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|perf|test|chore|ci|build|revert|security|i18n|accessibility|ui|database|config)(\(.+\))?: .+"

if ! echo "$commit_msg" | grep -qE "$pattern"; then
    echo "❌ Invalid commit message format!"
    echo ""
    echo "Format: <emoji> <type>(<scope>): <description>"
    echo ""
    echo "Examples:"
    echo "  ✨ feat(auth): add login button"
    echo "  🐛 fix(table): resolve pagination bug"
    echo "  ♻️ refactor(utils): extract common logic"
    exit 1
fi
```

